**NeoVim
Vim-Plug
  PlugInstall()
  PlugUpdate()
  PlugClean()      Remove unused plugins
  PlugUpgrade()    Update vim-plug

call NumberToggle()

Ack [options] {pattern} [{directories}]
search recursively in {directories} (which defaults to the current directory) for the {pattern}.
http://beyondgrep.com/documentation/
gv will open in vertical split
t opens in tab

Ctrl-p search for file
Ctrl-n NERDTreeToggle
Ctrl-^ Switch to last file

NERDTreeToggle:
t opens file in new tab
i for horizontal split
s for vert split
R for refresh

CtrlP Vim:
<C-v> open in new vsplit
<C-x> open in new split
<C-t> open in new tab

pwd

cs {old surround} {new surround}
Replace old surround symbol with new surround symbol, cursor must be on the segment being modified

g-Ctrl-g to see location
= will reformat tabs in the indicated block (gg = G reformats whole file)

**Bash/Iterm2
ag {pattern} [{directories}]

find {directory} -name {pattern}
recursively searches for a file

**Git
git checkout -t origin/master -b your-branch
git config --global push.default current
git add -p

**Tmux
prefix + Ctrl-s save session
prefix + Ctrl-r restore session
prefix + :source-file <conf_file> to source conf file
prefix + Ctrl-I install plugins
